{
  "text": "The influence of the smooth contours can be seen in Fig. 4 . It is visible that the proposed algorithm adds a smooth transition between the volume and the real scene. This method can be easily integrated with the F+C method proposed by Bichlmeier et al. [CITATION_1] , where \u03b2 will be the maximum between the value obtained from our method and the method proposed in [CITATION_2] . An example of the result of the proposed integration can be seen in Fig. 5 . Taking advantage from the clipping effect, we propose another two methods for F+C visualization, now based on visible background. In these methods, we take advantage from the type of scanning (CT or MRI) to enable new ways for physicians to explore the medical data on the patient.",
  "citation_candidates": [
